processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: Minimal Processing. Some material remains in original file folders.

otherfindaid.head: Other Finding Aids note
otherfindaid.p: For other Journal of General Physiology records currently open for research see:
FA925 Rockefeller University records, Rockefeller University Press, Journal of General Physiology, Editorial Correspondence, Series 2.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation note
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 25 years old are open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Contains manuscripts and associated correspondence concerning manuscripts, including general correspondence as well as editorial correspondence.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Completion of a use permission agreement is required prior to accessing the Journal of General Physiology records. See Archivist for details.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: This material was transferred to RAC as 15 accessions during the period 1982-2004.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Often includes general correspondence as well as editorial correspondence. Files in the 1990s-2000 may include various versions of the manuscript.
